 \Gamma(n,z) = \Gamma(n) e^{-z} \sum_{m=0}^{n-1} \frac{z^m}{m!}  \\  n=1,2,... 
 \Gamma(n+\frac{1}{2},z) 
 \Gamma(\frac{1}{2},z) = \sqrt{\pi} erfc(\sqrt{z}) 
n
 \Gamma(1/2+n, t) = \text{pochhammer}(1/2,n) \sqrt{\pi}\; \text{erfc}(\sqrt{t}) +  t^{n-1/2} e^{-t} \sum_{k=0}^{n-1} \text{pochhammer}(1/2-n,k) (-t)^{-k} 
\text{pochhammer}(1/2,k) = 2^{1-2k} \dfrac{(2k-1)!}{(k-1)!}
